description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Clinical Team Leader (RMN/RNLD) &lt;/strong&gt;with a passion for delivering the best quality of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working 40 hours per week at Cygnet Pindar House.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Pindar House&lt;/strong&gt; is our new 22 bed Neuropsychiatric rehabilitation facility for men affected by acquired brain injuries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to enjoy excellent career prospects while reaping the rewards of making a difference to others – every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day-to-Day…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise the smooth running of a shift and take leadership responsibility for the service in the absence of the Clinical Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a role model to all staff in clinical areas, helping to maintain a motivated and positive workforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take professional responsibility as a named nurse for the risk assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation of care needs for service users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in adherence to the NMC code and meet the requirements of revalidation as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a lead role as part of the Multi-Disciplinary Team to support implementation of the treatments &amp; therapy as per the service user’s care plans, meeting the physical &amp; emotional needs of the service users in a helpful, honest, responsible, respectful and empathic manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a leading role in monitoring &amp; maintaining physical wellbeing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively develop, coach and mentor staff to improve practice on the ward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow Cygnet Health Care policies and Procedures and maintain level of service, which meets the standard for the hospital and the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS and employee discount scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% NMC registration renewal paid by Cygnet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCNi membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bespoke career pathways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company paid Life Assurance scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plus many more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced Registered Mental Health (RMN)/ Learning Disability Nurse (RNLD) with a current Pin Number&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to maintain documentation, undertake audits and demonstrate integrity in your role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well informed of the Mental Health Act 1983 &amp; have an understanding of latest nursing practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to patient recovery in order to effectively monitor, manage and reduce risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compassion, resilience and a dedication to empower and support service user independence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to deputise in the absence of the Clinical Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in leadership, research and assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Health Care&lt;/strong&gt; has been providing a national network of high quality specialist mental health services for 30 years&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Pindar House&lt;/strong&gt; is a safe and secure place to aid recovery as well as offering those diagnosed with a progressive neurological disease, like Huntington’s disease, a caring and long term placement to support and help manage the progression of their symptoms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is a modern purpose built facility that has been designed specifically to provide a clinically led evidence based neuropsychiatric pathway for those individuals presenting with behaviours that challenge. Our focus is to create a therapeutic rich environment which engages our service users and offers them the opportunity to minimise their challenging behaviour and maximise their independence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What next?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you care about making a difference – we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Click the link to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
